{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"25c0763d-4fd2-4b46-a824-10ef953c1937","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n   Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner for MSTest.Sdk 3.8+, so removing `UseVSTest` is sufficient.\n\n2. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly execute the test binary (Microsoft.Testing.Platform builds a self-contained test host).\n\n3. **CLI differences** to be aware of:\n   - `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same) but syntax details may differ.\n   - `--logger` flags change — e.g., use `--report-trx` for TRX output instead of `--logger trx`.\n   - Use `dotnet test -- --help` to see the new platform's options.\n\n4. If you use **`.runsettings`**, pass it via `--settings <path>` (still supported).\n\n5. If you rely on **VSTest adapters/extensions**, verify they have Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents — not all third-party adapters are compatible.\n\nThat's it — the SDK handles the rest. No additional NuGet packages are needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"09cba249-a89a-449b-9747-f7975c0dcb82","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a code change task. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":401},"id":"45b1ddfb-0c31-4a8b-94e1-7ced2254309a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:04:40.861Z","parentId":"706970b4-209e-481d-98ac-cc2f2d084cc9"}
